anguage><Type>RoomTypes</Type><Text>Spain - Catalonia - Girona - Costa Brava - Baix Empordà - Begur. On reaching Begur, follow signs to Sa Riera beach. Once on the road to Sa Riera, guests will see a stop sign in the middle of a sharp right curve after about 100 metres. Take the road to the left (direction Playa del Racó and Pals) to find the convent on the right hand side after 500 m. By car: Motorway A7 Barcelona/France, exit 6 (Girona Nord), in the direction of Palamós/La Bisbal, exit 9 (Platja d'Aro/Lloret) in the direction of Platja d'Arao/Palafrugell. By plane: Aeropuerto del Prat - Barcelona (BCN) about 135 km away, Aeropuerto Girona Costa Brava around 45 km. By train: Estación (station) de Flaça some 35 km away. By bus: Bus company SARFA from Barcelona estación del nord (Arc de Triomf). From Girona: by bus transfer. By boat: Puerto/Port de Palamós Puerto/Port de l'Estartit.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>Constructed in 1730, the hotel comprises a total of 25 rooms, of which one is a single and two are suites. Amongst the air-conditioned business hotel's facilities count a foyer with 24-hour reception, a bar, a café, restaurant, conference facilities, and a TV lounge. Further offerings include the public Internet connection, a W-LAN access point, and both room and laundry services. Bicycle hire is also available, and there is parking for those arriving by car. Today, the natural terraces around the convent are the perfect place to enjoy its tranquillity: somewhere to read a good book in the shade of a cypress or take a refreshing swim in the pool. The original structure of the building has been maintained, together with the special ambience that evolved there. The chapel has been converted into a library with information about the region and its inhabitants. There is also an area for students of nature conservation.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Sauna</Code><Text>Sauna</Text></Amenity><Amenity><